---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="In-House Design | Bravura Builders"
  description="A complete design package from first concept to construction-ready documents. Renderings, plans, and specs that are yours to keep."
>
  <section class="page-hero dark on-dark">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow hero-load">In-house design &middot; Paid service</span>
      <h1><span class="line"><span>Design, A to Z. Yours to keep.</span></span></h1>
      <p class="lede hero-load d1">
        A complete design package from first concept to construction-ready documents. It&rsquo;s a
        standalone, paid engagement: if you build with Bravura, your builder already knows every
        detail. If you don&rsquo;t, the drawings go with you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-head rv">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Deliverables</span>
          <h2>What a design engagement includes.</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="deliv stagger">
        <div class="deliv-card rv">
          <span class="n">A</span><h3>Concept &amp; style boards</h3><p>
            Direction, materials, and finishes pinned down before anything is drawn.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="deliv-card rv">
          <span class="n">B</span><h3>3D renderings</h3><p>
            Photoreal views of your space so decisions happen on screen, not on site.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="deliv-card rv">
          <span class="n">C</span><h3>Plans &amp; specifications</h3><p>
            Dimensioned drawings and specs a crew can actually build from.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="deliv-card rv">
          <span class="n">D</span><h3>Construction documents</h3><p>
            The full package, ready for permits and pricing, with any builder.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="price-note rv" style="margin-top:34px">
        <span class="i" aria-hidden="true">$</span>
        <span
          ><b>Design is a paid service,</b> priced per engagement and payable even if you don&rsquo;t
          build with Bravura. What you pay for is what you keep: a complete, portable design package.</span
        >
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-head rv">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">From our design studio</span>
          <h2>Recent renderings.</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="render-grid stagger">
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/image1.jpg"
            alt="3D rendering of a primary bathroom in sage green with marble floors and brass fixtures"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Primary bath concept</b><span>Sage bath</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/image2.jpg"
            alt="3D rendering of the sage green primary bath with freestanding tub and vanities"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Tub &amp; double vanity</b><span>Sage bath</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/image3.jpg"
            alt="3D rendering of a freestanding tub beneath a window in a sage green bathroom"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Window wall</b><span>Sage bath</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Final_Render__1.jpg"
            alt="3D rendering of a bathroom vanity with wood cabinets and marble floor"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Vanity elevation</b><span>Marble bath</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Final_Render__2.jpg"
            alt="3D rendering of a marble bathroom passage with tile walls"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Wet-room passage</b><span>Marble bath</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Final_Render_3.jpg"
            alt="3D rendering of a walk-in shower with brass rain head and glass mosaic accent wall"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Walk-in shower study</b><span>Marble bath</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Final_Render__4.jpg"
            alt="3D rendering looking down the marble bath toward the shower with brass fixtures"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Shower approach</b><span>Marble bath</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Final_Render__5.jpg"
            alt="3D rendering of the marble bathroom entry with glass partition"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Entry &amp; glass partition</b><span>Marble bath</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-head rv">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Behind the renders</span>
          <h2>Every space starts as a working model.</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="lede" style="max-width:44ch;color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:16px">
          Rooms are modeled in 3D first, so layout, millwork, and appliances are agreed before the
          renders and before demolition.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-grid stagger">
        <figure class="m rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Untitled.jpg"
            alt="3D working model of a kitchen, overhead dollhouse view"
            loading="lazy"
          /><figcaption>Kitchen &middot; massing model</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="m rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Untitled2.jpg"
            alt="3D working model of a kitchen in perspective with tan cabinets and dark island"
            loading="lazy"
          /><figcaption>Kitchen &middot; perspective</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="m rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Untitled1_copy.jpg"
            alt="3D working model of a kitchen elevation"
            loading="lazy"
          /><figcaption>Kitchen &middot; elevation</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="m rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Untitled3.jpg"
            alt="Flat elevation study of the kitchen cabinetry run"
            loading="lazy"
          /><figcaption>Kitchen &middot; cabinetry run</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="m rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/Untitled1.jpg"
            alt="3D working model of the sage bathroom floor plan"
            loading="lazy"
          /><figcaption>Sage bath &middot; plan model</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="m rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/shot1.jpg"
            alt="3D working model of a laundry room with fluted wood wall, first view"
            loading="lazy"
          /><figcaption>Laundry &middot; model view 1</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="m rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/shot2.jpg"
            alt="3D working model of a laundry room with fluted wood wall and stacked machines"
            loading="lazy"
          /><figcaption>Laundry &middot; model view 2</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <figure class="m rv">
          <img
            src="/img/projects/IMG_2931.jpg"
            alt="Finished under-cabinet lighting detail in a built kitchen"
            loading="lazy"
          /><figcaption>Detail &middot; as built</figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="sec-head rv">
        <div>
          <span class="eyebrow">Modeled, then built</span>
          <h2>The model on the left. The room on the right.</h2>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="pair-grid stagger">
        <div class="card model-side rv">
          <img
            src="/img/renders/shot2.jpg"
            alt="3D working model of the laundry room design"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Laundry room</b><span>Working model</span></div>
        </div>
        <div class="card rv">
          <img
            src="/img/projects/IMG_2354.jpg"
            alt="The finished laundry room with fluted wood wall and stacked washer and dryer"
            loading="lazy"
          /><div class="cap"><b>Laundry room</b><span>As built</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="cta-band" style="padding-top:0">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="cta-box rv">
        <div>
          <h2>Start with design.</h2>
          <p>Tell us about the space and we&rsquo;ll scope your design engagement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="actions">
          <a class="btn blue" href="/contact">Start with design <span class="arr">&rarr;</span></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
